content:
I think it's a great attempt, they have put a lot of thought into this when 
it especially comes to professional music producers with midi support,I 
would love it if it can be more customizable, important: you need a good 
mic connected to whatever device you're using.
replyContent:
Thank you so much!
What custom options are you looking for?
Of course an external mic helps but a quiet environment and the device mic is more than enough to get your melodies down.

content:
It's not bad but it could do with some improvements regarding the pitch and 
transient detection. Perhaps a function to tell the app when a note or hit 
starts and ends. Playback can also get buggy when using the menu system 
too. In the right environment (I.e. My acoustically treated studio) it 
works fine, but I could use any number of more powerful music making tools. 
For this to be truly a great app it needs to have better detection when 
there is audible background noise so I can use it out and about, I think 
some simple gate functions would help this considerably. In my humble 
opinion this app has some huge potential but is not quite there yet. Please 
keep going!!! :)
replyContent:
Thank you very much for your great feedback!
User function to set start and end time is a great idea.
User menu interrupting playback: Will try to find a device like yours to test on but we have tested this running smoothly on much less powerful devices.
Background noise: Like you said you just need a quiet place and it works.
Thanks again!
